IT Budget




Warner Music Group Corp. is a music content company.{BR}{BR}It owns a number of record labels in the US and overseas, and also includes Warner/Chappell Music Group, a music publishing subsidiary. The company was bought by Access Industries in 2011.
Warner Music Group Corp. is a music content company.

It owns a number of record labels in the US and overseas, and also includes Warner/Chappell Music Group, a music publishing subsidiary. The company was bought by Access Industries in 2011.

IT at… MoreWarner Music Group Corp. is a music content company.

It owns a number of record labels in the US and overseas, and also includes Warner/Chappell Music Group, a music publishing subsidiary. The company was bought by Access Industries in 2011.

IT at Warner Music Group Corporation is evenly split between the New York, NY headquarters and the company's Burbank, CA location. IT staff are present at other company locations, such as in Nashville, TN, Los Angeles, CA and Miami Beach, FL. The Global IT Services group maintains the company's infrastructure, and includes Networks and telecommunications functions, as well as Enterprise Services and System Applications. 

The Technical Services group has oversight of several of these functions. The Security and Operations division oversees managers in charge of governance and Data Protection, among other security needs. Some of these functions are outsourced through HCL. The Office of IT Projects and Planning includes Project Management functions. 

The Customer Care group heads the company's internal help desk and provides ITIL management. Other IT divisions are responsible for Global Office Applications and Project Management. Vendor Management is handled from the New York offices. IT at subsidiary Warner/Chappell Music, based in Los Angeles, CA, is headed by a CIO. A newer subsidiary is Rhino Records.





